latestPosts.caption:
For Cannes 2025, @masoomminawala graced the red carpet in a custom Arpita Mehta creation — a look that honoured Indian craftsmanship in its most refined form.

This wasn’t just fashion; it was storytelling.
Rooted in traditional mirrorwork, the ensemble reflected heritage not just as embellishment, but as a symbol of protection, reflection, and joy.

The soft gold and beige palette whispered quiet elegance, while the sheesha embroidery played beautifully with light and geometry.
Modern in silhouette, yet deeply tied to tradition — it was a celebration of Indian artistry reimagined for the world stage.

A handcrafted, gold-plated bag inspired by sacred Indian motifs completed the look, carrying a piece of home to Cannes.

Rooted. Refined. Real.
